This article is a press briefing by Press Secretary Jay Carney. The briefing covers a range of topics including President Obama's plans to answer questions on Twitter about extending middle-class tax cuts, a bilateral meeting with the Prime Minister of Bulgaria, a speech at the National Defense University, and the President's congratulations to the Duke and Duchess of Cambridge on their pregnancy. Carney also discusses the security situation in Syria and the President's position on extending tax cuts for the top 2% of Americans. He addresses concerns about the fiscal cliff negotiations and the President's plan for deficit reduction, as well as his commitment to securing loose nuclear materials and weapons.